Class And

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.nyu.cs.addressbook.search.impl.And
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SearchCriteria

    public class And
extends Object
implements SearchCriteria
    Author:
    shenli

    The And class represents criteria information.

    The specified criteria is the element should match all criteria(s). And objects are not constant; their values could be changed after they are created. Because And objects are implemented by synchronized list they could be shared.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object o)
        Compares the specified object with this And object for equality. Returns true if and only if the specified object is also an And object, both objects have the same criteria list.

        This implementation first checks if the specified object is this And. If so, it returns true; if not, it checks if the specified object is an And object. If not, it returns false; if so, it iterates over both And objects, comparing corresponding fields. If any comparison returns false, this method returns false. Otherwise it returns true when the iterations complete.
